replies.bodyText:
@benradey if you check encoding, after running uploader script, you will find, it's always ISO_8859_1, There is no use of this conditional block with current code, as it will never execute.
secondly, if you check com.redhat.pantheon.servlet.ServletUtils#handleParamAsStream(org.apache.sling.api.SlingHttpServletRequest, java.lang.String, java.util.function.Function<java.io.InputStream,R>) , line no 184, you can see, we are parsing content in UTF_8 while storing it in nodes.
Accordingly, i understand, we can go ahead by removing this block, to fix the encoding issue.

